label: Heat Crimes
description: Turntablist and composer Mariam Rezaei completes her ambitious, pithy triptych with 'BOWN', her debut for the Heat Crimes imprint. Flipping the concept of turntable-based music on its head, she fractures free jazz, noise, death drone and operatic fragments into a broken tangle of spinbacks, pitchbends, loping rhythms and perverted side-eyes. As half-Hungarian, half-Romanian, he lived near the border in Cluj, a city with a healthy music culture which had spawned important prog rock bands incuding Cromatic, Experimental Quintet and Semnal M.
